The internet’s favorite number is changing.










In 2025, *67* has eclipsed *69* in Google search popularity. This week [Dictionary.com](https://www.dictionary.com/e/word-of-the-year-2025/) declared *67* its Word of the Year, which inspired me to make this plot.  

If you don’t know what *67* is, read [Dictionary.com’s article](https://www.dictionary.com/e/word-of-the-year-2025/) or this [Wall Street Journal piece](https://www.wsj.com/lifestyle/six-seven-meme-teens-math-teachers-42764bcb?gaa_at=eafs&gaa_n=AWEtsqcev_D8mIi7PAXApQ9kaAJ73Xs6p4sLS-hpk4ghpXxLS65GP4KR3MitEf1hcWk%3D&gaa_ts=6907f43c&gaa_sig=p7-bm8dw0ZM0OKOAek07YkV2ylhjb9YY_3E2Ey3ts-exxxp-xzPLH1CwTfZmzEKu_9CTG6LUmtxCJP5g-cbErw%3D%3D).  
If you don’t know what *69* is, see [Urban Dictionary](https://www.urbandictionary.com/define.php?term=69).
